044-001 Ipiatlak m̃aat iskei kin ga ipo .
§ 044-002 Iwelkia ipato elag Ep̃uf sanpe kin ipo mai .
It was up at Pufa [behind Montmartre] and it came. It came
the small islands that come right up to Eratap there.
Imai me imai kin ipato teflan ga kin ifiskotkot § 044-003 naur
seserik nen kin rumai pan pan pan tkal Ertap sanie .
And the two islands there, one which they call Kap̃um lep and the other is Kap̃um rik.
§ 044-004 Go naur inru kin ratu sanie , rusos , rusos kaaru ki Kap̃umlep ko kaaru ipi Kap̃umrik .
And these two islands, this snake wanted to split them.
§ 044-005 Go naur nra nen , me m̃aat ina ifisktofir .
There is the point at Eter, it is a long point, and this snake split it.
§ 044-006 Ipiatlak nagis ni Eter ga ipi nagis pram , me m̃aat nen kin ifisktofi .
That's why it is short now. But the point at Etmat is a long one, the point at Etmat which is where we are now.
§ 044-007 Ipi nlaken kipe m̃it . Me nagis ni Etmat m̃as
kin ipram , nagis ni Etmat kin akit tutkos to .
Etmat point. But the point at Emut and the point at Eter are there.
§ 044-008 Nagis ni Etmat . Me nagis ni Emut kin
ito , go nagis ni Eter wan kin me iptau .
The point at Emut which is in line with the two islands there. Because its face, its face, that is this point at Emut.
§ 044-009 Nagis ni Emut nen kin ileg ki naur sees nra ne .
Nlaken kin nakon , nakon wan ki kin nagis ni Emut ne .
Its face there. M̃aatleplep is the name of the snake. He's the one who split them into two small islands there.
§ 044-010 Me nakon kin . M̃aatleplep ina nagi
m̃aat nen ki rusoso ki M̃aatleplep . Ga kin
ifisktofi kin rapi naur sees inru pato .
They call them Kap̃um rik and Kap̃um lep. That's it.
The Erakor side I can talk about. But I can't talk about the Eratap side because it belongs to people from Erarap. OK.
§ 044-012 Nanre ni Erakor kin ato tli , me akano til nanre ni
Ertap nlaken ga me ni ipi Ertap ntan . ni Ore nam̃er .
